04/05/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The chairman of the BiH Serb Republic People's Assembly, Dragan Kalinic, and Serbia-Montenegro's Ambassador to BiH, Stanimir Vukicevic, met on Friday (2 May) in Banja Luka. They discussed common efforts in the fight against organised crime and corruption, agreeing that these are the two major threats to the economic and political stability of the region. They also reviewed opportunities to intensify parliamentary co-operation. (SRNA - 02/05/03)
